# Install PWA

This guide will help you install Echo as a Progressive Web App (PWA) on your device.

## Why Install PWA?

- **App-like experience** - Opens in full screen without browser chrome
- **Offline support** - Works without internet connection
- **Quick access** - Launch from your home screen or desktop

---

## Install on Desktop (Chrome / Edge)

### Step 1: Visit Echo

Open [Echo](https://echo.yuler.ai) in Chrome or Edge browser.

![Chrome address bar showing install icon](https://developer.chrome.com/static/docs/image/pwa-install-address-bar_a2f8c4d9d4.png)

### Step 2: Look for Install Icon

In the right side of the address bar, you'll see an install icon (computer with arrow).

![Install prompt in Chrome](https://developer.chrome.com/static/docs/image/pwa-install-prompt_0b1ff363c4.png)

### Step 3: Click Install

Click the icon and select **"Install Echo"** in the dialog that appears.

### Step 4: Launch

Echo will open in a standalone window. You can find it in your Applications folder or Start menu.

---

## Install on iPhone / iPad (Safari)

### Step 1: Visit Echo

Open [Echo](https://echo.yuler.ai) in Safari.

### Step 2: Tap Share Button

Tap the **Share** button (square with arrow) at the bottom of the screen.

![iOS Share button](https://support.apple.com/library/content/dam/edam/applecare/images/en_US/iOS/ios17-iphone15-share-sheet.jpg)

### Step 3: Add to Home Screen

Scroll down and tap **"Add to Home Screen"**.

![iOS Add to Home Screen option](https://support.apple.com/library/content/dam/edam/applecare/images/en_US/iOS/ios17-iphone15-add-to-home-screen.jpg)

### Step 4: Confirm

Tap **"Add"** in the top right corner. Echo will appear on your home screen.

---

## Install on Android (Chrome)

### Step 1: Visit Echo

Open [Echo](https://echo.yuler.ai) in Chrome.

### Step 2: Open Menu

Tap the three dots menu in the top right corner.

### Step 3: Select Install

Tap **"Add to Home Screen"** or **"Install App"**.

### Step 4: Confirm

Follow the prompts to install. Echo will be added to your apps list.

---

## Troubleshooting

### Install button doesn't appear

- Make sure you're using **HTTPS** (or localhost)
- Use a supported browser: Chrome, Edge, or Safari
- Refresh the page and try again

### Need help?

If you encounter any issues, feel free to ask in the comments.
